rmfollow is a script to ...

follow a symlink and delete it's destination file(s) including any other symlinks it points to intermediately
removes any *empty* directories containing the symlink(s)/files which might be left over after deleting the destination file
(and finally ... ) removes the symlink specified in the argument at the command line


